{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Artificial intelligence (AI) and generative AI that make use of large language models (LLMs) like ChatGPT are a hot topic.",
    "From their impact on academic integrity in higher education (Rudolph et al. 2023) to utility in improving programming scripts (Perkel 2023),",
    "the new technology has fast gained traction and emblazoned further debate on the use of artificial intelligence (AI) in academic research and education.",
    "In this paper, we show that ChatGPT and other generative AI-utilizing LLMs are technological developments that can play a role in interpretive qualitative research.",
    "Technological developments have historically shaped the way qualitative research is conducted; from the advent of computers (Brent 1984), the introduction of word processing files (Freidheim 1984), and software for qualitative analysis (Shelly & Sibert, 1986) to more recent innovations like Zoom and its use in qualitative interviewing (Archibald et al., 2018) and automatic coding in qualitative software like NVivo and ATLAS.ti (Kalpokas & Radivojevic, 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "From their impact on academic integrity in higher education (Rudolph et al. 2023) to utility in improving programming scripts (Perkel 2023),",
    "Technological developments have historically shaped the way qualitative research is conducted; from the advent of computers (Brent 1984), the introduction of word processing files (Freidheim 1984), and software for qualitative analysis (Shelly & Sibert, 1986) to more recent innovations like Zoom and its use in qualitative interviewing (Archibald et al., 2018) and automatic coding in qualitative software like NVivo and ATLAS.ti (Kalpokas & Radivojevic, 2022)."
  ]
